attachments.fallback: David Keatts updated the description of Partner deck counts vs partner rank is confusing.
attachments.text:
Left: <https://dev.edhrec.com/commanders/tana-the-bloodsower>
Right: <https://edhrec.com/commanders/tana-the-bloodsower-tymna-the-weaver>

Left "329 decks" includes solo Tana as long as partner Tana (any combo), but the rank #845 is only Tana solo.

Compared to the right, there are fewer Tana/Tymna decks than Tana/X decks (obviously), but the Tana/Tymna rank is higher.

Seems a bit confusing, should we change this?  I'm not sure we should actually change anything, but I did want to ask.  My initial thought was to change the page from Tana/X decks to Tana/null decks, but that would be changing the content of the page itself... so idk.
